inlineContent.text: Each app is allowed to create a single filter configuration. The

The filter configuration is stored in the Network Extension preferences which are managed by the Network Extension framework. The filter configuration must be explicitly loaded into memory from the Network Extension preferences before it can be used, and any changes must be explicitly saved to the Network Extension preferences before taking effect on the system.

In product builds for distribution, Network Content Filter configurations can be created only on supervised devices. During development and testing you can temporarily override this restriction by signing your build with the
class, you must enable the Network Extensions capability in Xcode and select the Content Filter capability. See
